input2: 35 yo female with s/p uncomplicated term SVD presented on PPD#9 to the ED from PCP office with 4 days of chest pain, increasing pleuritic SOB and with exertion, orthopnea, and headache.  Chest pain of gradual onset, central, nonradiating, different from GERD. BP was 158/77 in the ED. Headache started at base of her neck, has wrapped around forehead in band-like distribution.  No vision changes, RUQ or epigastric pain.  Bleeding minimal.  ROS positive for increasing bilateral lower extremity swelling over past few days.
